BALLADS

xxv CHEVY CHACE THE HUNTING

GOD prosper long our noble king, Our lives and safeties all3

A woeful hunting once there did In Chevy-Chace befall 3

To drive the deer with hound and horn Erle Percy took his way3

The child may rue that is unborn, The hunting os that day.

The stout Erle of Northumberland A vow to God did make,

His pleasure in the Scottish woods Three summer’s days to take,

The chiefest harts in Chevy-Chace To kill and bear away.

These tydings to Erle Douglas came, In Scotland where he lay:

Who sent Erle Percy present word, He wold prevent his sport.

The English Erle, not fearing that, Did to the woods resort
